generalCommentData.message: Could you please annotate returns types and parameters of (at least) public methods as @Nullable and @NotNull? Believe me, it will save you from a lot of NPEs. It will also save time of these methods callers who will always know the nullity part of the contract. Kotlin has even introduced special behavior and special language constructs for the NPE problem. But these annotations in Java are quite handy as well. Why don't you use them?

versionedLineCommentData.message: public interface => javadoc is appreciated. I'm not a fan of javadocs: I hate trivial javadocs and I never declare @param tags for obvious parameters (like Project). But a short note about what this class/method should do won't hurt. Something like: {quote}Handles an event reported by the SVN native client during commit. Example of such events is file status change: "Adding file test.txt"{quote}

versionedLineCommentData.message: --Why do we need to sort paths?-- I see: because we get {{paths\[0]}} later. Then you must remember that Arrays.sort will sort your paths lexicographically. It may give unexpected results on case insensitive systems, if you want the "most upper" directory appear at the first place.
